  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A medical device study to assess the clinical accuracy and equivalence to reference devices
      of the SVSS to satisfy the requirements of the recognised applicable international standards.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The SVSS is designed to measure and display 5 vital signs: pulse rate, blood oxygen
      saturation (Sp02), blood pressure, body temperature and respiration rate. These results will
      be compared for accuracy with the results obtained using standard vital sign measurement
      equipment on the same subject.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
